1
00:01:42,319 --> 00:01:43,200
Take a photo with Auntie.

2
00:01:44,159 --> 00:01:45,519
For the memories.

3
00:01:45,519 --> 00:01:46,680
You finally came back.

4
00:01:48,200 --> 00:01:48,640
Come on.

5
00:01:50,359 --> 00:01:51,719
One, two, three.

6
00:01:52,079 --> 00:01:52,519
Good.
Okay.

7
00:01:53,519 --> 00:01:54,599
Stay here for a bit.

8
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:55,680
I'll go cook.

9
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:10,879
Ye is back.

10
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:13,360
First, you need to
solve the issue here.

11
00:02:14,039 --> 00:02:14,800
Only after that,

12
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:16,120
you could bring this on.

13
00:02:16,439 --> 00:02:18,039
Pay attention to the ratio

14
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:19,120
between the front and the rear.

15
00:02:19,599 --> 00:02:20,520
Go back and compare it
with that plan again.

16
00:02:21,439 --> 00:02:22,599
Okay. Thanks, Engineer Xing.

17
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:35,599
Booked the earliest flight tomorrow.

18
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:40,240
Look at these dishes.

19
00:02:40,719 --> 00:02:42,199
See if they're still your favorites.

20
00:02:42,919 --> 00:02:44,000
Now,

21
00:02:44,120 --> 00:02:45,759
I don't cook with lard anymore.

22
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,080
So don't worry. Eat up.

23
00:02:47,879 --> 00:02:49,960
I've missed this taste.

24
00:02:50,879 --> 00:02:51,360
It's just...

25
00:02:51,919 --> 00:02:53,280
Isn't it too much?

26
00:02:53,319 --> 00:02:54,280
The two of us can't finish it.

27
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:56,280
Here in Zhazhating,

28
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:58,759
food never goes unfinished.

29
00:02:59,120 --> 00:02:59,599
Come on.

30
00:03:00,240 --> 00:03:00,840
Lanfang.

31
00:03:01,280 --> 00:03:01,840
Fangfang.

32
00:03:02,319 --> 00:03:02,759
Right on time.

33
00:03:02,759 --> 00:03:04,599
Auntie Shanxi. Auntie Yufen.

34
00:03:04,639 --> 00:03:05,280
Ye.

35
00:03:05,599 --> 00:03:06,599
It's been so long.

36
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:07,520
Sit down. Sit down.

37
00:03:08,159 --> 00:03:09,919
What a feast you two made.

38
00:03:10,319 --> 00:03:11,360
Great.

39
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,599
Food is all ready for us.

40
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,439
Eat, eat. I'm starving.

41
00:03:16,199 --> 00:03:16,520
Thank you.

42
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:17,680
The food is good today.

43
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:18,280
Not bad.

44
00:03:19,199 --> 00:03:19,560
Here.
Ye.

45
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:22,599
At Big G's wedding, it was packed.

46
00:03:22,599 --> 00:03:23,759
We didn't get to talk to you.

47
00:03:24,159 --> 00:03:25,560
Today, let's have a proper chat.

48
00:03:25,639 --> 00:03:26,800
Yes. Today,

49
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:28,840
let's drink and catch up properly.

50
00:03:29,719 --> 00:03:31,400
I was just talking with Lanfang

51
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,400
about a project.

52
00:03:32,759 --> 00:03:33,680
This time,

53
00:03:33,879 --> 00:03:34,520
I came with

54
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:36,159
a rural-support project for Chang Island.

55
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:37,800
My company

56
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:39,439
wants to expand

57
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:40,680
Chang Island's industrial chain.

58
00:03:44,439 --> 00:03:46,280
This is the planning report.

59
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:49,000
This is wonderful, Ye.

60
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:50,879
We're thinking the same thing.

61
00:03:51,159 --> 00:03:51,599
Really.

62
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:52,879
I've noticed lately

63
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:55,120
Livestreams for local farmers are a hit.

64
00:03:55,560 --> 00:03:56,280
I was thinking

65
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:57,439
whether I could

66
00:03:57,840 --> 00:03:58,719
try livestreaming too.

67
00:03:59,599 --> 00:04:01,280
We have so much seafood here.

68
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:03,120
I could show everyone

69
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:04,400
how to cook seafood

70
00:04:04,439 --> 00:04:05,159
and how to eat it.

71
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:07,719
My seafood noodles...

72
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:09,800
Can I turn them into a brand?

73
00:04:10,039 --> 00:04:11,240
Of course you can.

74
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:13,360
Livestream e-commerce is huge now.

75
00:04:13,439 --> 00:04:14,719
You can livestream and sell products.

76
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:15,680
It could even make
Zhazhating popular.

77
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:17,319
Exactly.

78
00:04:17,399 --> 00:04:19,120
If you really start livestreaming,

79
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,399
I'll send viewers to your stream.

80
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:22,680
Although

81
00:04:22,720 --> 00:04:24,279
I don't have that many followers,

82
00:04:24,439 --> 00:04:25,680
I'll still send viewers your way.

83
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:28,439
Lanfang, you're a big influencer.

84
00:04:29,439 --> 00:04:30,600
50,000 followers, a real influencer!

85
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:33,839
If you really go live,

86
00:04:33,959 --> 00:04:35,319
I'll be there to click likes

87
00:04:35,519 --> 00:04:36,560
and gifts.

88
00:04:36,639 --> 00:04:37,519
I'll send you sports cars.

89
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:38,279
Yufen.
Oh my.

90
00:04:38,959 --> 00:04:39,720
So generous.
Absolutely.

91
00:04:40,639 --> 00:04:41,519
Auntie Shanxi,
are you starting

92
00:04:42,399 --> 00:04:43,439
a second act in your career?

93
00:04:44,279 --> 00:04:44,879
I support you.

94
00:04:45,279 --> 00:04:46,639
No second act.

95
00:04:46,839 --> 00:04:49,120
Mainly, Ye, you inspired me.

96
00:04:49,439 --> 00:04:50,600
And isn't the country

97
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:51,199
strongly developing

98
00:04:51,199 --> 00:04:52,519
the marine economy now?

99
00:04:52,959 --> 00:04:54,120
We should do our part.

100
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:54,800
Absolutely.

101
00:04:54,959 --> 00:04:57,199
The three beauties of Zhazhating,

102
00:04:57,519 --> 00:04:59,240
if you want to do something,

103
00:04:59,399 --> 00:05:00,959
there's nothing you can't do.

104
00:05:01,040 --> 00:05:01,920
Yes, yes.

105
00:05:02,079 --> 00:05:02,439
Right.
Come on.

106
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:03,879
To the three beauties.
Good.

107
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:06,439
Cheers.

108
00:06:01,519 --> 00:06:02,720
Of course you do.

109
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:04,839
When you fix phones,

110
00:06:04,839 --> 00:06:05,759
you're always looking down.

111
00:06:06,199 --> 00:06:07,240
That's bad for your neck.

112
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:13,439
Fine.

113
00:06:14,319 --> 00:06:15,519
Then I'll wear it.

114
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:28,519
Auntie.

115
00:06:31,519 --> 00:06:32,160
Auntie.

116
00:06:41,079 --> 00:06:43,079
[Ye, I've got errands in town.]

117
00:06:43,439 --> 00:06:45,120
[Sandwiches and coffee are in the fridge.]

118
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:46,680
[I left the key on the table.]

119
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:48,399
[I may stay at the shop tonight.]

120
00:06:48,720 --> 00:06:49,839
[Remember to lock the door if you go out.]

121
00:06:56,160 --> 00:06:56,839
Fix your hair.

122
00:06:59,879 --> 00:07:00,399
Okay.

123
00:07:01,439 --> 00:07:04,079
Three, two, one.

124
00:07:04,519 --> 00:07:05,879
Cheese.

125
00:07:06,639 --> 00:07:08,240
Good. Very good. One more.

126
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:09,600
You, come this way a little.

127
00:07:10,279 --> 00:07:11,839
Okay, everyone look at the camera.

128
00:07:16,519 --> 00:07:19,040
Three, two, one.

129
00:07:19,399 --> 00:07:20,720
Cheese.

130
00:07:35,839 --> 00:07:37,759
Go! Go! Go!

131
00:07:37,759 --> 00:07:38,319
Qing Ye.

132
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:42,000
Go!

133
00:07:43,360 --> 00:07:44,000
Run forward.

134
00:07:45,600 --> 00:07:46,160
Catch up.

135
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:54,079
Go!

136
00:08:50,759 --> 00:08:51,799
I'll see you off here.

137
00:08:52,279 --> 00:08:53,039
Good luck.
Thanks.

138
00:08:53,919 --> 00:08:54,399
Good luck.

139
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:57,639
Qing Ye.

140
00:08:58,600 --> 00:08:59,200
Qing Ye.

141
00:09:15,159 --> 00:09:16,159
In this love story

142
00:09:16,159 --> 00:09:17,799
of reunions and near misses,

143
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:20,000
instead of missing each other once more,

144
00:09:20,759 --> 00:09:21,840
why not stop

145
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:23,360
and return to the lighthouse

146
00:09:23,519 --> 00:09:24,840
where we first met?

147
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:27,759
She'll follow the tide of memory

148
00:09:28,039 --> 00:09:28,879
back to you.

149
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:30,720
Sometimes,

150
00:09:31,279 --> 00:09:31,879
only when you slow down

151
00:09:32,720 --> 00:09:34,320
can the right person find you.

152
00:11:47,799 --> 00:11:48,919
When I first met Xing Wu,

153
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:50,799
I thought he was just

154
00:11:50,799 --> 00:11:52,320
with a wild, spiky haircut,

155
00:11:52,799 --> 00:11:54,559
a prickly rebel.

156
00:11:56,159 --> 00:11:57,200
After he became my cousin,

157
00:11:58,360 --> 00:11:59,840
he installed a door lock for me

158
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:01,320
and put in an air conditioner, without asking.

159
00:12:02,279 --> 00:12:03,519
If we had

160
00:12:03,519 --> 00:12:04,720
half a chilled watermelon,

161
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:05,639
it would be perfect.

162
00:12:08,519 --> 00:12:08,960
Eat up.

163
00:12:14,279 --> 00:12:16,159
He stepped forward when I was in danger.

164
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:17,919
Qing Ye, it's me.

165
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:19,799
He became the family I could rely on most.

166
00:12:20,919 --> 00:12:21,960
If you're willing,

167
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:23,960
you can come back to Zhazhating with me.

168
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:25,919
My home is your home.

169
00:12:27,159 --> 00:12:28,720
When I was at my most helpless,

170
00:12:30,120 --> 00:12:31,720
he gave me the warmest support.

171
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:35,120
I hope the next time

172
00:12:35,120 --> 00:12:36,000
we meet,

173
00:12:37,559 --> 00:12:39,080
we'll both be our best selves.

174
00:12:39,440 --> 00:12:41,240
Only when reality separated us

175
00:12:41,840 --> 00:12:42,720
did I understand

176
00:12:43,919 --> 00:12:45,559
that my feelings for him

177
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:48,000
had long gone beyond family.

178
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:50,240
They had turned into love.

179
00:12:51,879 --> 00:12:53,679
Fate brought us together again.

180
00:12:54,799 --> 00:12:56,039
In that moment, I finally knew

181
00:12:57,159 --> 00:12:58,639
he was the most dazzling light

182
00:12:59,080 --> 00:13:00,440
in my life.

183
00:13:31,279 --> 00:13:32,519
Actually, I've always wanted to ask you.

184
00:13:33,320 --> 00:13:34,120
Back then,

185
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:35,519
why didn't you apply directly

186
00:13:35,519 --> 00:13:36,440
to a school in Beijing?

187
00:13:37,039 --> 00:13:37,879
In my repeat year,

188
00:13:37,879 --> 00:13:39,960
a professor from a top aerospace school
contacted me.

189
00:13:40,519 --> 00:13:41,360
He said he admired the
aircraft model I made.

190
00:13:42,759 --> 00:13:43,639
The one you made back then...

191
00:13:43,639 --> 00:13:44,679
for Ye Yingjian?

192
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:45,120
Yes.

193
00:13:45,679 --> 00:13:46,879
That model later won an award.

194
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:48,559
Ye Yingjian gave the award back to me.

195
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:51,120
The professor from that school

196
00:13:51,159 --> 00:13:52,720
strongly recommended it.

197
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:54,879
That way, you could study

198
00:13:54,879 --> 00:13:56,200
the major you really liked.

199
00:13:57,840 --> 00:13:58,799
If my grades stood out,

200
00:13:58,799 --> 00:14:00,000
you could enter an integrated program

201
00:14:00,919 --> 00:14:02,320
and work on top projects

202
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:03,159
in aerospace.

203
00:14:04,399 --> 00:14:04,840
Yes.

204
00:14:05,200 --> 00:14:06,240
The prospects were better too.

205
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:09,279
I gave myself four years

206
00:14:09,279 --> 00:14:10,279
to dig deep into my field,

207
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:12,639
to earn the chance

208
00:14:12,799 --> 00:14:13,799
to work on projects in Beijing,

209
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:16,000
and be able to stand beside you.

210
00:14:16,840 --> 00:14:17,639
Only then would I feel

211
00:14:17,639 --> 00:14:18,679
I could truly stand beside you.

212
00:14:23,879 --> 00:14:24,559
Back then,

213
00:14:25,519 --> 00:14:26,720
I heard from Shi Min

214
00:14:27,639 --> 00:14:28,879
you applied to that aerospace school.

215
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:31,320
But I really didn't know

216
00:14:32,120 --> 00:14:33,720
there was so much behind it.

217
00:14:36,759 --> 00:14:37,799
Actually, that year,

218
00:14:39,039 --> 00:14:40,240
I went to Beijing to find you.

219
00:14:42,039 --> 00:14:42,840
You looked for me?

220
00:14:44,600 --> 00:14:46,159
But your school was strict.

221
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:47,759
I couldn't get in.

222
00:14:48,559 --> 00:14:49,519
But I still waited until I saw you.

223
00:14:50,519 --> 00:14:51,679
I heard your roommates say

224
00:14:52,679 --> 00:14:53,799
you won first place

225
00:14:53,799 --> 00:14:54,519
in the English debate

226
00:14:55,360 --> 00:14:56,639
and got a national scholarship.

227
00:14:58,519 --> 00:14:59,879
You could have contacted me.

228
00:15:02,120 --> 00:15:03,240
I still had a long way

229
00:15:03,720 --> 00:15:04,440
to go.

230
00:15:05,679 --> 00:15:06,360
You said

231
00:15:07,279 --> 00:15:08,679
you wouldn't stop for anyone.

232
00:15:10,080 --> 00:15:11,080
I didn't want you

233
00:15:11,679 --> 00:15:12,600
to slow down for me either.

234
00:15:20,279 --> 00:15:21,279
Then from now on,

235
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:24,039
we'll walk the road together.

236
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:46,000
Why did you keep this?

237
00:15:46,159 --> 00:15:47,320
To buy you a house.

238
00:15:49,159 --> 00:15:50,360
You said that. Did you forget?

239
00:15:51,120 --> 00:15:52,559
When did I say that?

240
00:15:53,120 --> 00:15:54,200
You said it right there.

241
00:15:55,720 --> 00:15:56,559
Come on.

242
00:15:57,120 --> 00:15:58,159
Imperial green, right?

243
00:15:58,360 --> 00:15:59,159
Sell it.

244
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:00,799
Once we sell it,

245
00:16:01,399 --> 00:16:03,519
we can live in a big villa.

246
00:16:05,519 --> 00:16:06,519
I was drunk.
I was talking nonsense.

247
00:16:07,679 --> 00:16:08,320
I don't care.

248
00:16:08,919 --> 00:16:09,840
I took it seriously anyway.

249
00:16:20,639 --> 00:16:21,200
Cao Ping.

250
00:16:23,240 --> 00:16:24,159
Xing Wu.

251
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:25,200
Why are you back?

252
00:16:25,879 --> 00:16:27,559
I was delivering goods nearby,

253
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:28,759
so I brought you two boxes of seafood.

254
00:16:29,279 --> 00:16:29,799
Thank you.
Thanks.
No problem.

255
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:33,799
It really has been years.

256
00:16:34,240 --> 00:16:35,000
Compared with before,
you're completely different.

257
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:36,960
Of course.

258
00:16:37,200 --> 00:16:38,279
He's now

259
00:16:38,279 --> 00:16:39,960
Manager Cao of Shi Family Seafood.

260
00:16:40,039 --> 00:16:40,879
Everything on Chang Island
is handled by him.

261
00:16:42,039 --> 00:16:42,799
That impressive?

262
00:16:43,799 --> 00:16:44,799
I knew you can do great things.

263
00:16:44,919 --> 00:16:45,519
Cao Ping,

264
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,600
come look at my TV.

265
00:16:47,600 --> 00:16:48,440
The screen keeps glitching.

266
00:16:48,879 --> 00:16:49,440
Cao Ping,

267
00:16:49,679 --> 00:16:50,679
my air conditioner isn't cooling.

268
00:16:50,720 --> 00:16:51,919
Can you check it when you have time?

269
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:53,320
Sure. I'll come by later.

270
00:16:53,519 --> 00:16:54,120
Hurry, okay?
Thanks.

271
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:56,120
Ever since you left,

272
00:16:56,279 --> 00:16:57,399
I've taken over all this work.

273
00:16:57,919 --> 00:16:59,120
Actually, I used to envy you.

274
00:16:59,360 --> 00:17:00,080
You knew a bit of everything.

275
00:17:00,519 --> 00:17:02,039
So I studied some things myself

276
00:17:02,039 --> 00:17:02,600
and helped everyone out.

277
00:17:02,799 --> 00:17:04,240
I worried that after I left,

278
00:17:04,240 --> 00:17:05,319
there'd be no one left

279
00:17:05,319 --> 00:17:06,039
to handle repairs in Zhazhating.

280
00:17:06,519 --> 00:17:07,559
I didn't expect you to take over.

281
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:09,039
Now that you're back,
I'll give the work back to you.

282
00:17:09,839 --> 00:17:10,480
I won't fight you for it.
Okay?

283
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:12,599
By the way,

284
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:13,920
are you free later?

285
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:15,599
Let's have a little match.

286
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:17,519
What are you two doing?
Match in what?

287
00:17:19,559 --> 00:17:20,079
Relax.

288
00:17:20,519 --> 00:17:21,759
Purely a technical contest.

289
00:17:49,240 --> 00:17:49,759
Here we go.

290
00:17:51,680 --> 00:17:52,160
Tell me.

291
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:54,000
What are we competing in?

292
00:17:55,079 --> 00:17:55,880
How about push-ups?

293
00:17:58,039 --> 00:17:59,160
Ready, start.

294
00:18:01,880 --> 00:18:04,400
Four, five, six, seven.

295
00:18:07,880 --> 00:18:09,799
Twenty, twenty-one, twenty-two.

296
00:18:10,039 --> 00:18:12,920
Twenty-three, twenty-four,
twenty-five, twenty-six.

297
00:18:35,200 --> 00:18:37,000
Fifty-eight, fifty-nine.

298
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:38,920
Sixty.

299
00:18:41,680 --> 00:18:42,319
Congratulations.

300
00:18:43,519 --> 00:18:44,000
You won.

301
00:18:45,440 --> 00:18:46,519
You let me win, didn't you?

302
00:18:48,839 --> 00:18:49,640
A loss is a loss.

303
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:50,960
A win is a win.

304
00:18:55,759 --> 00:18:57,599
Next time, let's try something else.

305
00:18:58,279 --> 00:18:59,039
Then next time,

306
00:18:59,319 --> 00:18:59,960
I'll still win.

307
00:19:05,599 --> 00:19:06,279
But

308
00:19:08,240 --> 00:19:09,039
in life,
is anything ever absolute?

309
00:19:09,839 --> 00:19:10,519
Right, Xing Wu?

310
00:19:18,799 --> 00:19:19,359
Xing Wu.

311
00:19:24,400 --> 00:19:25,119
I'm sorry.

312
00:19:37,960 --> 00:19:39,200
Some people are like

313
00:19:39,799 --> 00:19:41,319
another version of ourselves.

314
00:19:41,839 --> 00:19:42,599
The clashes

315
00:19:42,599 --> 00:19:44,440
that once kept me up at night

316
00:19:45,240 --> 00:19:46,559
had softened with time

317
00:19:47,119 --> 00:19:47,880
and become the strength

318
00:19:48,559 --> 00:19:50,039
that carried me forward.

319
00:19:58,359 --> 00:19:59,000
I'm back.

320
00:20:02,160 --> 00:20:02,839
Where's Cao Ping?

321
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:05,240
He said he'd go back to Chang Island

322
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:06,119
after fixing the appliances.

323
00:20:07,519 --> 00:20:08,119
How was it?

324
00:20:08,559 --> 00:20:09,160
Who won?

325
00:20:09,839 --> 00:20:10,599
Of course, me.

326
00:20:11,359 --> 00:20:12,519
Nothing happened between you two, right?

327
00:20:13,359 --> 00:20:13,960
No.

328
00:20:14,359 --> 00:20:16,000
He just said he owed me an apology.

329
00:20:16,759 --> 00:20:17,319
It's been five years.

330
00:20:17,960 --> 00:20:18,640
Seeing everyone

331
00:20:18,640 --> 00:20:19,960
moving in a better direction,

332
00:20:20,359 --> 00:20:20,960
I'm happy for him.

333
00:20:22,960 --> 00:20:23,920
I'm happy for you too.

334
00:20:25,880 --> 00:20:26,400
Hungry?

335
00:20:27,880 --> 00:20:28,559
I'll cook.

336
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:31,079
My boyfriend is going
to cook for me himself?

337
00:20:32,039 --> 00:20:32,599
Absolutely.

338
00:20:33,039 --> 00:20:33,680
You haven't been
eating properly in Beijing, have you?

339
00:20:34,720 --> 00:20:36,079
I have, sort of.

340
00:20:37,640 --> 00:20:39,039
Small restaurants downstairs,

341
00:20:39,319 --> 00:20:40,599
the company cafeteria,

342
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:42,200
mall restaurants,

343
00:20:42,720 --> 00:20:43,880
and takeout sometimes.

344
00:20:44,279 --> 00:20:45,240
Don't always eat takeout.

345
00:20:45,759 --> 00:20:46,599
You need to eat properly.
Got it?

346
00:20:48,039 --> 00:20:48,720
Got it.

347
00:20:49,400 --> 00:20:50,799
Then shouldn't you make it

348
00:20:50,799 --> 00:20:52,359
Michelin-chef level?

349
00:20:54,319 --> 00:20:54,759
Okay.

350
00:20:55,359 --> 00:20:56,720
For you, I'll learn to cook.

351
00:20:57,079 --> 00:20:58,440
Chinese and Western, alternating.

352
00:20:59,559 --> 00:21:00,359
That's more like it.

353
00:21:00,839 --> 00:21:01,680
Then I'll wait to eat.
Okay. Wait for it.

354
00:21:10,359 --> 00:21:11,160
Help me tie my apron.

355
00:21:19,519 --> 00:21:20,359
Don't tie it too tight.

356
00:21:22,599 --> 00:21:23,279
Don't worry.

357
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:24,759
So I won't delay
my chance to eat good food,

358
00:21:26,440 --> 00:21:27,279
I tied you

359
00:21:27,279 --> 00:21:28,680
a nice loose bow.

360
00:21:38,799 --> 00:21:39,359
Hello?

361
00:21:40,119 --> 00:21:40,839
I knew long ago

362
00:21:40,839 --> 00:21:41,920
something was up with you and Xing Wu.

363
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:42,880
There must be a story.

364
00:21:43,319 --> 00:21:43,799
Tell me.

365
00:21:44,079 --> 00:21:45,279
How far have you two gone?

366
00:21:45,720 --> 00:21:48,839
Just holding hands and hugging.

367
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:50,000
Have you kissed?

368
00:21:53,839 --> 00:21:54,880
Not bad.

369
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:55,640
How many times?

370
00:21:56,160 --> 00:21:56,920
Once.

371
00:21:57,359 --> 00:21:58,160
Only once?

372
00:21:59,240 --> 00:22:00,960
Don't underestimate that once.

373
00:22:01,559 --> 00:22:02,640
It may have been just once,

374
00:22:03,160 --> 00:22:05,519
but it lasted from sunset till dark.

375
00:22:05,640 --> 00:22:06,680
A whole hour.

376
00:22:07,799 --> 00:22:09,640
Qing Ye, you two are amazing.

377
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:10,960
Get out of here.

378
00:22:22,839 --> 00:22:23,359
Hello?
Xing Wu.

379
00:22:24,279 --> 00:22:24,960
Congratulations.
Official congrats

380
00:22:25,960 --> 00:22:27,119
from the whole team

381
00:22:27,359 --> 00:22:29,079
and our best wishes.

382
00:22:29,559 --> 00:22:30,640
You found out so fast?

383
00:22:31,279 --> 00:22:32,200
My sister told me.

384
00:22:32,599 --> 00:22:33,160
She almost shattered

385
00:22:33,160 --> 00:22:34,200
my eardrums.

386
00:22:34,880 --> 00:22:35,599
You're about to shatter

387
00:22:35,599 --> 00:22:36,680
mine too.

388
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:38,079
All right. I won't talk now.

389
00:22:38,079 --> 00:22:38,680
I'm busy.

390
00:22:39,039 --> 00:22:40,000
Don't brush me off.

391
00:22:40,279 --> 00:22:41,400
If you two get married,

392
00:22:41,559 --> 00:22:43,279
my sister and I get head-table seats.

393
00:22:43,599 --> 00:22:44,359
Sure, sure.

394
00:22:44,359 --> 00:22:45,440
Sit wherever you want.

395
00:22:45,960 --> 00:22:46,519
Hanging up.

396
00:23:07,279 --> 00:23:08,119
Take a break.

397
00:23:08,440 --> 00:23:09,039
Eat first.

398
00:23:09,759 --> 00:23:10,240
Soon.

399
00:24:17,759 --> 00:24:19,039
Where did you get that hair tie?

400
00:24:22,519 --> 00:24:23,720
A girl left it here.

401
00:24:24,680 --> 00:24:25,599
A girl?

402
00:24:28,960 --> 00:24:29,559
Are you mad?

403
00:24:31,440 --> 00:24:32,359
When was this?

404
00:24:33,279 --> 00:24:33,680
Who?

405
00:24:34,279 --> 00:24:34,960
Come clean.

406
00:24:37,519 --> 00:24:38,599
This girl is called

407
00:24:39,359 --> 00:24:39,920
Qing Ye.

408
00:24:41,279 --> 00:24:42,920
Five years ago, she left this hair tie

409
00:24:43,160 --> 00:24:44,200
in Zhazhating.

410
00:25:56,680 --> 00:25:57,799
It's been so long,

411
00:25:59,240 --> 00:26:00,119
and you still kept it.

412
00:26:01,799 --> 00:26:02,759
Because anything of yours

413
00:26:03,759 --> 00:26:04,559
is precious

414
00:26:05,279 --> 00:26:06,079
to me.

415
00:26:09,240 --> 00:26:10,160
I want a reward.

416
00:26:22,839 --> 00:26:23,599
Bro Wu.

417
00:26:27,640 --> 00:26:28,160
Bro Wu.

418
00:26:30,200 --> 00:26:31,200
Why are you here?

419
00:26:31,759 --> 00:26:33,599
We came to congratulate you.

420
00:26:33,640 --> 00:26:34,960
What perfect timing.

421
00:26:38,720 --> 00:26:40,039
You... you guys...

422
00:26:40,359 --> 00:26:41,039
You told them?

423
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:42,200
I didn't say anything.

424
00:26:42,640 --> 00:26:43,079
Then...

425
00:26:43,559 --> 00:26:45,079
then how did you know?

426
00:27:14,799 --> 00:27:15,440
Here, here, here.

427
00:27:17,640 --> 00:27:19,279
So that's how.

428
00:27:20,519 --> 00:27:21,079
Bro Wu,

429
00:27:22,039 --> 00:27:23,319
not bad.

430
00:27:23,559 --> 00:27:24,519
After all these years,
we finally get couple content.

431
00:27:28,839 --> 00:27:30,000
You're Boss Hao now,

432
00:27:30,200 --> 00:27:31,519
and you still remember the wild dog thing?

433
00:27:32,039 --> 00:27:33,119
I'm just happy.

434
00:27:33,519 --> 00:27:34,200
I officially announce

435
00:27:34,519 --> 00:27:35,960
you two are my favorite ship

436
00:27:35,960 --> 00:27:37,319
this year.

437
00:27:37,680 --> 00:27:39,240
I'm so happy, Qing Ye.

438
00:27:39,519 --> 00:27:40,079
See?

439
00:27:40,279 --> 00:27:41,319
The luck from the bouquet

440
00:27:41,319 --> 00:27:42,680
did pass on to you.

441
00:27:43,039 --> 00:27:44,440
I hope you and Bro Wu

442
00:27:44,440 --> 00:27:45,720
will end up together.

443
00:27:45,880 --> 00:27:46,559
Thank you.

444
00:27:46,559 --> 00:27:47,839
You even came all this way.

445
00:27:48,160 --> 00:27:48,759
Let's toast.

446
00:27:48,960 --> 00:27:50,400
Here's to happiness, love,

447
00:27:50,839 --> 00:27:52,799
and better days ahead.

448
00:27:53,079 --> 00:27:54,519
And, uh, may your career thrive.

449
00:27:56,559 --> 00:27:57,720
Come on, cheers, cheers.

450
00:27:57,839 --> 00:27:59,160
Cheers.

451
00:28:05,680 --> 00:28:06,519
Manager Qing,

452
00:28:07,359 --> 00:28:08,240
you're really busy.

453
00:28:09,880 --> 00:28:11,519
Mine are small matters.

454
00:28:11,519 --> 00:28:12,599
How can I compare with you?

455
00:28:13,200 --> 00:28:14,279
Your work

456
00:28:14,279 --> 00:28:15,279
literally goes up into the sky.

457
00:28:16,519 --> 00:28:17,599
Go ahead and tease me.

458
00:28:19,119 --> 00:28:20,559
I'm telling the truth.

459
00:28:23,680 --> 00:28:24,799
I guess you're not wrong.

460
00:28:32,359 --> 00:28:33,240
I'll pick you up tonight.

461
00:28:34,880 --> 00:28:35,920
You're not working overtime today, right?

462
00:28:36,119 --> 00:28:36,680
No overtime.

463
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:38,440
Okay. I'm going to the company.

464
00:28:42,519 --> 00:28:42,960
Bye.
Bye.

465
00:28:52,119 --> 00:28:53,200
The due diligence on Chang Island

466
00:28:53,319 --> 00:28:54,240
is going very smoothly.

467
00:28:54,680 --> 00:28:55,519
The aquaculture farm owners

468
00:28:55,519 --> 00:28:56,880
are all highly willing to cooperate.

469
00:28:57,200 --> 00:28:58,160
We've completed the survey.

470
00:28:58,240 --> 00:28:59,400
It's already in the final stage.

471
00:29:01,359 --> 00:29:02,160
Qing Ye,

472
00:29:02,519 --> 00:29:03,680
I truly admire

473
00:29:03,680 --> 00:29:04,920
your ability to find gold.

474
00:29:06,440 --> 00:29:07,519
Whether our group can win

475
00:29:07,519 --> 00:29:08,519
the top prize internally this year

476
00:29:08,799 --> 00:29:09,880
depends on how wide

477
00:29:09,960 --> 00:29:10,799
you can cast this net.

478
00:29:11,359 --> 00:29:12,079
Don't worry, boss.

479
00:29:12,279 --> 00:29:13,319
I'll do my best.

480
00:29:13,640 --> 00:29:14,319
That issue from last time
has been solved, right?

481
00:29:15,119 --> 00:29:15,880
It's solved.

482
00:29:16,759 --> 00:29:17,759
Any other problems now?

483
00:29:21,200 --> 00:29:21,920
The project Professor Lu
assigned to your side...

484
00:29:23,359 --> 00:29:24,920
How far along are you now?

485
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:25,640
I'm at about
fifty percent.

486
00:29:42,799 --> 00:29:44,279
Finally finished.

487
00:29:45,039 --> 00:29:45,960
We're home too.

488
00:29:46,759 --> 00:29:47,799
I'm exhausted.

489
00:29:47,799 --> 00:29:49,279
Battery drained.

490
00:29:50,319 --> 00:29:50,880
I can't walk anymore.

491
00:29:53,119 --> 00:29:53,920
You don't have to walk.

492
00:30:05,559 --> 00:30:06,000
Come here.

493
00:30:11,720 --> 00:30:12,519
What do you want for dinner?

494
00:30:13,079 --> 00:30:13,960
Seafood noodles.

495
00:30:14,480 --> 00:30:14,920
Seafood noodles.

496
00:30:15,319 --> 00:30:16,000
What else?

497
00:30:16,640 --> 00:30:17,559
Sea urchin egg custard.

498
00:30:31,519 --> 00:30:31,960
Dad.

499
00:30:32,519 --> 00:30:33,160
Hello, Uncle.

500
00:30:36,200 --> 00:30:37,000
Wait for me a second.

501
00:30:59,160 --> 00:31:00,440
I really like Xing Wu.

502
00:31:01,759 --> 00:31:03,359
I'm happy being with him.

503
00:31:03,960 --> 00:31:04,960
I can tell.

504
00:31:06,799 --> 00:31:08,279
You insisted on staying in Beijing.

505
00:31:08,279 --> 00:31:09,119
Was it because of him?

506
00:31:12,359 --> 00:31:13,279
Not entirely.

507
00:31:13,880 --> 00:31:15,519
I made that decision

508
00:31:15,839 --> 00:31:17,119
after thinking carefully

509
00:31:17,440 --> 00:31:18,519
about my future.

510
00:31:20,319 --> 00:31:21,000
When I brought you

511
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:22,400
back from Zhazhating,

512
00:31:23,359 --> 00:31:24,640
I lent their family some money.

513
00:31:24,640 --> 00:31:25,240
Did you know that?

514
00:31:31,519 --> 00:31:32,400
A few years later,

515
00:31:32,400 --> 00:31:33,519
he gave me this card.

516
00:31:33,880 --> 00:31:35,000
There was 150,000 in it.

517
00:31:35,880 --> 00:31:36,839
He paid back everything

518
00:31:36,839 --> 00:31:37,920
the money I gave his family

519
00:31:37,960 --> 00:31:39,559
for taking care of you,

520
00:31:40,200 --> 00:31:41,039
plus the Xuan Island renovation costs,

521
00:31:41,839 --> 00:31:42,960
with interest, all in one payment.

522
00:31:49,240 --> 00:31:49,680
He...

523
00:31:50,880 --> 00:31:52,400
Where did he get so much money?

524
00:31:55,200 --> 00:31:56,720
He said it was

525
00:31:56,720 --> 00:31:57,359
patent royalties from those years.

526
00:31:58,200 --> 00:31:59,240
But you can imagine

527
00:32:00,240 --> 00:32:01,079
it must also have been money

528
00:32:01,640 --> 00:32:03,200
he saved by living frugally.

529
00:32:05,880 --> 00:32:07,000
After all,

530
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:08,039
I failed in my own marriage too.

531
00:32:09,079 --> 00:32:11,519
Who you date is your decision.

532
00:32:12,279 --> 00:32:13,440
I won't interfere too much.

533
00:32:15,039 --> 00:32:16,920
But one fact can't be denied.

534
00:32:18,440 --> 00:32:20,039
There are real gaps

535
00:32:20,079 --> 00:32:21,160
between our two families

536
00:32:21,680 --> 00:32:23,519
in many ways.

537
00:32:27,400 --> 00:32:28,240
I'm worried

538
00:32:28,880 --> 00:32:29,880
that as you spend time together,

539
00:32:29,880 --> 00:32:31,440
you'll face many conflicts.

540
00:32:44,160 --> 00:32:45,759
To catch up with my pace,

541
00:32:46,200 --> 00:32:47,119
he was willing to wait five years.

542
00:32:48,440 --> 00:32:49,440
So I believe,

543
00:32:50,240 --> 00:32:51,119
no matter what,

544
00:32:52,400 --> 00:32:53,839
he'll work hard enough

545
00:32:53,839 --> 00:32:55,000
to bridge every gap.

546
00:33:13,359 --> 00:33:14,279
What did your dad say?

547
00:33:14,839 --> 00:33:15,920
He's not angry, is he?

548
00:33:17,720 --> 00:33:18,319
No.

549
00:33:19,000 --> 00:33:19,640
Let's talk when we get home.

550
00:33:20,079 --> 00:33:20,559
Come on.

551
00:33:37,400 --> 00:33:38,559
What are you making for me?

552
00:33:39,960 --> 00:33:40,680
Seafood noodles.

553
00:33:45,519 --> 00:33:47,559
Can you make baked pumpkin custard?

554
00:33:50,359 --> 00:33:51,000
I'll look it up.

555
00:33:59,839 --> 00:34:00,839
Do you have lemons at home?

556
00:34:01,319 --> 00:34:02,039
Maybe in the fridge.

557
00:34:08,199 --> 00:34:08,719
Are there any?

558
00:34:10,400 --> 00:34:11,159
I can't find them.

559
00:34:22,119 --> 00:34:22,719
Found them?

560
00:34:24,039 --> 00:34:27,360
I found milk and white sugar.

561
00:34:28,039 --> 00:34:28,679
Will that work?

562
00:35:03,199 --> 00:35:04,199
It's so good.

563
00:35:04,679 --> 00:35:05,760
I didn't know Beibei pumpkin

564
00:35:05,760 --> 00:35:06,639
could be made this way.

565
00:35:07,440 --> 00:35:08,679
I'll make it for you whenever you want.

566
00:35:08,719 --> 00:35:09,119
Okay.

567
00:35:13,480 --> 00:35:14,519
I only found out today

568
00:35:15,199 --> 00:35:16,840
that you've been repaying money for years.

569
00:35:18,079 --> 00:35:18,559
If my dad

570
00:35:18,760 --> 00:35:20,119
hadn't told me today,

571
00:35:20,519 --> 00:35:21,440
were you

572
00:35:21,760 --> 00:35:22,800
never going to tell me?

573
00:35:24,960 --> 00:35:25,880
Your dad told you everything?

574
00:35:28,760 --> 00:35:30,159
Most of it was

575
00:35:30,159 --> 00:35:31,920
scholarship money from school,

576
00:35:32,360 --> 00:35:33,280
patent royalties and things like that.

577
00:35:33,679 --> 00:35:34,320
It's not worth mentioning.

578
00:35:37,440 --> 00:35:38,119
Xing Wu.

579
00:35:39,599 --> 00:35:40,840
You've had a hard time all these years.

580
00:35:43,400 --> 00:35:44,639
What else did your dad tell you?

581
00:35:45,280 --> 00:35:47,360
Was he strongly against

582
00:35:47,360 --> 00:35:48,119
us being together?

583
00:35:50,639 --> 00:35:53,360
Not against it,

584
00:35:55,000 --> 00:35:56,159
but not exactly supportive either.

585
00:35:56,960 --> 00:35:57,599
It's just...

586
00:35:58,440 --> 00:36:00,320
he's still a little worried.

587
00:36:23,840 --> 00:36:25,360
To catch up with my pace,

588
00:36:25,800 --> 00:36:26,760
he was willing to wait five years.

589
00:36:28,079 --> 00:36:29,119
So I believe,

590
00:36:30,159 --> 00:36:31,039
no matter what,

591
00:36:32,320 --> 00:36:33,360
in the future,

592
00:36:33,360 --> 00:36:34,920
he'll work hard to bridge every gap.

593
00:36:36,960 --> 00:36:38,519
Are you sure you won't regret it?

594
00:36:39,800 --> 00:36:40,639
In your words,

595
00:36:40,639 --> 00:36:42,199
you're dating down.

596
00:36:44,679 --> 00:36:45,639
For the same question,

597
00:36:46,800 --> 00:36:48,119
my mom had an answer too.

598
00:36:50,559 --> 00:36:51,199
She said

599
00:36:52,239 --> 00:36:53,440
Love is a bet you choose to make,

600
00:36:53,840 --> 00:36:55,199
and whatever happens, you own it.

601
00:36:56,119 --> 00:36:58,000
She gave it everything she had

602
00:36:58,400 --> 00:36:59,840
and stayed true to herself.

603
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:02,519
Even if it didn't work out,

604
00:37:03,679 --> 00:37:05,679
she never regretted having loved him.

605
00:37:13,239 --> 00:37:13,800
Qing Ye,

606
00:37:14,519 --> 00:37:15,559
in a few days,

607
00:37:15,800 --> 00:37:17,079
I plan to visit your dad.

608
00:37:18,280 --> 00:37:19,199
After all, with some things,

609
00:37:19,440 --> 00:37:20,519
taking the first step yourself

610
00:37:20,719 --> 00:37:21,880
is what shows real sincerity.

611
00:37:26,840 --> 00:37:28,280
Bring him home sometime.

612
00:37:29,360 --> 00:37:29,840
See?

613
00:37:31,639 --> 00:37:32,679
What a coincidence.

614
00:37:34,280 --> 00:37:35,440
He wants to meet you too.

615
00:37:40,639 --> 00:37:41,880
I've finally waited for this day.

616
00:37:42,679 --> 00:37:43,280
Don't worry.

617
00:37:43,760 --> 00:37:44,519
I'm ready.

618
00:37:47,639 --> 00:37:48,519
I believe in you.

619
00:37:49,199 --> 00:37:50,000
And I believe in myself.

620
00:37:51,320 --> 00:37:52,199
Come on. Cheers.

621
00:37:59,559 --> 00:38:00,519
Easy.

622
00:38:00,800 --> 00:38:01,760
You can't hold your liquor.

623
00:38:02,599 --> 00:38:03,679
How can you say I can't?

624
00:38:03,679 --> 00:38:04,519
That was before.

625
00:38:04,519 --> 00:38:05,719
Now I can drink really well.

626
00:38:08,159 --> 00:38:09,000
Do you remember what you're like
when you're drunk?

627
00:38:09,880 --> 00:38:10,639
In Zhazhating?

628
00:38:13,199 --> 00:38:13,800
What did I do?

629
00:38:13,960 --> 00:38:15,599
There was an abandoned boat by the sea.

630
00:38:16,400 --> 00:38:17,679
You insisted on dragging me onto it.

631
00:38:17,719 --> 00:38:19,039
You said, Captain, set sail.

632
00:38:19,280 --> 00:38:19,880
And called me

633
00:38:20,280 --> 00:38:20,920
Jack.

634
00:38:21,639 --> 00:38:22,760
Me, Rose.

635
00:38:23,039 --> 00:38:24,119
Jack.

636
00:38:25,239 --> 00:38:25,880
Rose.
Jack.

637
00:38:27,159 --> 00:38:27,679
Rose.
Did I?

638
00:38:28,519 --> 00:38:29,519
I did not. You did.
That was still the mild part.

639
00:38:30,440 --> 00:38:31,559
Then you

640
00:38:32,119 --> 00:38:33,119
insisted on performing for me.

641
00:38:33,519 --> 00:38:34,280
What did I perform?

642
00:38:35,159 --> 00:38:36,039
the Monkey King's birth scene.

643
00:38:43,320 --> 00:38:44,519
Don't give me a play-by-play.

644
00:38:44,519 --> 00:38:45,400
I hate when people do
drunk recaps.

645
00:38:45,920 --> 00:38:46,840
And the Little Swan dance.

646
00:38:47,559 --> 00:38:48,519
Good. Today,

647
00:38:49,519 --> 00:38:50,239
let's settle this.
Come on.

648
00:38:51,000 --> 00:38:51,440
Come on.
Come on.

649
00:39:12,679 --> 00:39:13,800
I want to build a plane.

650
00:39:14,159 --> 00:39:16,239
I want to build the biggest,

651
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:18,519
tallest plane.

652
00:39:18,760 --> 00:39:19,960
Do you know? From here,

653
00:39:20,519 --> 00:39:22,519
I can fly a paper plane to...

654
00:39:22,639 --> 00:39:23,239
To where?
Haidian.

655
00:39:24,079 --> 00:39:24,719
This is Haidian.

656
00:39:24,719 --> 00:39:26,000
You're flying to Haidian?

657
00:39:26,400 --> 00:39:27,760
Do you know, before,

658
00:39:28,920 --> 00:39:29,800
I wanted to fly.

659
00:39:30,039 --> 00:39:31,119
Now I don't.

660
00:39:31,360 --> 00:39:32,159
Then where do you want to go?

661
00:39:32,239 --> 00:39:33,440
Guess what I want to do now.

662
00:39:33,679 --> 00:39:34,360
I don't know.
Tell me.

663
00:39:35,679 --> 00:39:38,440
Now I want to leave Earth,

664
00:39:39,039 --> 00:39:39,880
fly into the universe,

665
00:39:40,719 --> 00:39:41,880
fly into outer space.

666
00:39:42,920 --> 00:39:43,760
Outer space?

667
00:39:44,239 --> 00:39:44,920
Where are you going?
Do you want to go?

668
00:39:46,599 --> 00:39:47,400
Will you take me?

669
00:39:47,760 --> 00:39:48,480
Of course.

670
00:39:49,000 --> 00:39:50,199
Of course I'll take you.

671
00:39:50,920 --> 00:39:51,360
Okay.

672
00:39:51,559 --> 00:39:52,400
Really?

673
00:39:52,440 --> 00:39:53,639
Of course it's real.

674
00:39:53,760 --> 00:39:55,679
I'll build a plane, then a rocket.

675
00:39:55,840 --> 00:39:56,920
Then we'll go to outer space.

676
00:39:57,079 --> 00:39:57,760
We'll elope.

677
00:39:58,679 --> 00:39:59,800
We're done playing on Earth.

678
00:40:00,239 --> 00:40:00,719
Okay.
I believe you.

679
00:40:01,639 --> 00:40:02,599
Can I believe you?

680
00:40:02,920 --> 00:40:04,400
When Jack says something,

681
00:40:04,679 --> 00:40:05,840
he means it.

682
00:40:06,280 --> 00:40:06,800
Good.

683
00:40:07,400 --> 00:40:08,320
Then from now on,

684
00:40:08,599 --> 00:40:10,039
Rose won't jump either.

685
00:40:10,280 --> 00:40:13,000
She'll follow Jack and fly.

686
00:40:13,719 --> 00:40:14,880
Fly.

687
00:40:15,119 --> 00:40:16,159
Fly.

688
00:40:16,519 --> 00:40:17,400
Fly.

689
00:40:18,760 --> 00:40:19,400
Fly.

690
00:40:22,000 --> 00:40:22,960
My old dream

691
00:40:22,960 --> 00:40:24,519
was to soar into the sky.

692
00:40:26,519 --> 00:40:27,159
Impressive.

693
00:40:27,559 --> 00:40:28,679
Do you want to soar into the sky?

694
00:40:29,159 --> 00:40:30,119
How would I soar into the sky?

695
00:40:30,719 --> 00:40:31,320
Climb up.

696
00:40:31,880 --> 00:40:32,519
Get down.

697
00:40:33,039 --> 00:40:33,639
Climb up.

698
00:40:33,679 --> 00:40:34,679
You'll fall.

699
00:40:36,239 --> 00:40:37,280
How do I soar into the sky?

700
00:40:51,840 --> 00:40:52,519
Nervous?

701
00:40:53,559 --> 00:40:54,159
A little.

702
00:40:54,840 --> 00:40:55,880
First time meeting the family.

703
00:40:55,920 --> 00:40:56,679
No experience.

704
00:40:57,400 --> 00:40:59,079
It's my first time bringing a boyfriend

705
00:40:59,119 --> 00:40:59,960
home to meet my dad too.

706
00:41:00,039 --> 00:41:01,119
I don't have much experience either.

707
00:41:01,960 --> 00:41:03,559
Then two negatives make a positive.

708
00:41:04,880 --> 00:41:05,599
What if my dad

709
00:41:06,079 --> 00:41:07,400
sets a trap for me?

710
00:41:08,599 --> 00:41:09,840
Then I'll elope with you.

711
00:41:11,400 --> 00:41:11,880
Not bad.

712
00:41:12,159 --> 00:41:13,079
I knew I chose the right person.

713
00:41:13,840 --> 00:41:14,280
Let's go.

714
00:41:20,320 --> 00:41:20,760
Dad.

715
00:41:21,239 --> 00:41:22,559
Mr. Qing, Ye is back.

716
00:41:22,840 --> 00:41:23,360
Hello, Mr. Qing.

717
00:41:29,039 --> 00:41:30,199
Give that to me. I'll carry it.

718
00:41:30,199 --> 00:41:31,039
Okay. Thank you.

719
00:41:32,119 --> 00:41:32,599
You're here.

720
00:41:34,519 --> 00:41:35,000
Do you have time?
Yes.

721
00:41:36,880 --> 00:41:37,559
Do me a favor.

722
00:41:41,239 --> 00:41:42,159
I'll go over first.

723
00:41:49,119 --> 00:41:49,599
Auntie,

724
00:41:49,760 --> 00:41:51,159
what has my dad been busy with lately?

725
00:41:51,559 --> 00:41:53,119
Lately,

726
00:41:53,119 --> 00:41:53,639
he's always in the garden.

727
00:41:55,039 --> 00:41:56,159
He started planting flowers.

728
00:42:02,519 --> 00:42:03,440
Do you know how to grow flowers?

729
00:42:04,559 --> 00:42:05,079
Uncle,

730
00:42:05,519 --> 00:42:06,880
I grew up in the countryside.

731
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:08,519
I've grown wheat and corn.

732
00:42:08,840 --> 00:42:10,119
I learned some basic gardening too.

733
00:42:10,360 --> 00:42:11,039
I can grow flowers.

734
00:42:11,920 --> 00:42:12,280
Right.

735
00:42:12,800 --> 00:42:14,280
The Welwitschia Qing Ye

736
00:42:14,280 --> 00:42:15,119
brought back to Zhazhating...
After the fire,

737
00:42:16,400 --> 00:42:17,320
I saved it.

738
00:42:21,039 --> 00:42:22,400
That Welwitschia is still alive?

739
00:42:22,920 --> 00:42:23,360
Yes.

740
00:42:29,320 --> 00:42:30,320
This garden

741
00:42:31,320 --> 00:42:32,119
used to be taken care of

742
00:42:32,119 --> 00:42:33,159
by Ye's mother.

743
00:42:33,840 --> 00:42:35,280
As for these flowers and plants,

744
00:42:35,519 --> 00:42:37,719
how much water, how deep to plant them,

745
00:42:37,719 --> 00:42:38,519
I can't figure it out.

746
00:42:39,119 --> 00:42:40,360
So I bought some seeds.

747
00:42:41,960 --> 00:42:42,840
I planted them four or five days ago,
but they still haven't sprouted.

748
00:42:43,639 --> 00:42:44,239
Take a look for me.

749
00:42:44,599 --> 00:42:45,719
What you planted is...

750
00:42:46,840 --> 00:42:47,360
Just these.

751
00:42:53,239 --> 00:42:54,519
Tulips aren't really suitable

752
00:42:54,519 --> 00:42:55,519
for summer planting.

753
00:42:55,880 --> 00:42:56,679
High temperatures

754
00:42:56,800 --> 00:42:58,159
affect their dormancy

755
00:42:58,159 --> 00:42:59,000
and flower-bud development.

756
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:01,400
This plumbago is more suitable.

757
00:43:01,880 --> 00:43:02,519
It likes to grow

758
00:43:02,519 --> 00:43:03,679
in places with plenty of sunlight.

759
00:43:04,519 --> 00:43:06,000
But when it gets too hot in summer,

760
00:43:06,280 --> 00:43:07,239
it also needs proper shade.

761
00:43:08,079 --> 00:43:08,760
Put it here.

762
00:43:11,679 --> 00:43:12,199
Looks like

763
00:43:12,880 --> 00:43:14,320
things with different natures

764
00:43:15,280 --> 00:43:16,400
shouldn't be forced together.

765
00:43:17,679 --> 00:43:18,760
Then throw it away.

766
00:43:20,119 --> 00:43:20,760
No need for that.

767
00:43:22,800 --> 00:43:23,599
Uncle, how about this?

768
00:43:25,159 --> 00:43:26,199
We'll need some clay pebbles.
